  "faq": [
    {
      "question": "What is the difference between FUE and DHI hair transplants?",
      "answer": "FUE (Follicular Unit Extraction) uses robotic assistance to extract individual follicles, while DHI (Direct Hair Implantation) uses specialized Choi pens for direct implantation without pre-created channels. DHI has faster recovery (5-7 days vs 10+ days) and slightly higher graft survival rates, but both are permanent solutions."
    },
    {
      "question": "How long before I see results from a hair transplant?",
      "answer": "Hair typically sheds 1-3 months post-procedure (normal shedding phase). New growth begins at 3-4 months, becomes visible at 6-9 months, and full density is achieved at 12-18 months."
    },
    {
      "question": "Is PRP therapy effective for hair loss?",
      "answer": "PRP therapy is most effective for early to mid-stage hair loss. Results show 30-40% improvement in density on average, but effectiveness varies by individual. It's often combined with other treatments like medications or laser therapy."
    },
    {
      "question": "How many laser hair removal sessions are needed?",
      "answer": "Typically 6-8 sessions spaced 4-6 weeks apart are needed for 85-95% hair reduction. The exact number depends on hair type, skin type, and the treated area. Maintenance sessions (1-2 yearly) help maintain results."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the recovery time for laser skin resurfacing?",
      "answer": "Recovery depends on laser type: Ablative lasers (CO2, Erbium) have 5-7 days downtime, fractional lasers have 3-5 days, and non-ablative lasers have minimal to no downtime. Full results appear over 3-6 months."
    },
    {
      "question": "Are the results from acne laser treatment permanent?",
      "answer": "Laser treatment can significantly improve acne (50-70% reduction) and acne scars, but may require maintenance sessions. Results depend on ongoing skincare and sun protection."
    },
    {
      "question": "Can I combine hair and skin treatments?",
      "answer": "Yes, many treatments can be combined. For example, PRP can be used with hair transplants or alongside skin treatments. However, timing and healing periods must be carefully planned by your dermatologist."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the cost of a hair transplant?",
      "answer": "FUE costs ₹2,00,000-₹6,00,000+ depending on graft count and complexity. DHI is more expensive (₹3,00,000-₹8,00,000+) due to its advanced technique. Costs typically include consultation, surgery, and post-operative care."
    }
  ]
